<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF856A3BFA7C9A631AB4B934" lastPageId="127" lastPageNumber="886" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF856A3BFA7C9A631AB4B934" blockId="126.[1405,2612,3090,3212]" lastBlockId="127.[776,1370,288,715]" lastPageId="127" lastPageNumber="886" pageId="126" pageNumber="885">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AFA7C9A63186FB769" box="[1408,1647,3130,3163]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotophilus heathii</taxonomicName>
is genetically close to S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AF8409A631646B769" authorityName="Goodman, Jenkins &amp; Ratrimomanarivo" authorityYear="2005" box="[1980,2118,3130,3163]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tandrefana">tandrefana</taxonomicName>
and S. marovazain 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF856A3AF6AD9A6317F6B769" box="[2385,2550,3130,3163]" name="Madagascar" pageId="126" pageNumber="885">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and S. leucogasterin sub-Saharan Africa, being embedded in the African 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF856A3AF6DD9A3817AEB7B0" box="[2337,2478,3169,3202]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotophilus</taxonomicName>
clade unrelated to the widespread Asiatic species S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BFCD3971E1D7ABA5A" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1821" box="[815,890,327,360]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">kuhlii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BFC6C971E1A80BA5A" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[912,1152,327,360]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heathii">Scotophilus heathii</taxonomicName>
might include S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BFCD6972A1D9DBAA2" authorityName="Sody" authorityYear="1928" box="[810,925,371,400]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">celebensis</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies (heath, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BFAE7972A1D41BA8A" authorityName="Hall &amp; Jones" authorityYear="1961" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">insularis</taxonomicName>
, and watkinst) have been recognized, but there is no well-defined distribution for any subspecies. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="90EB6676FF856A3AFF7E9A86175DB6A4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398541" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398541" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398541/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="885" startId="126.[130,160,3295,3320]" targetBox="[11,2762,17,3657]" targetPageId="125">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF856A3AFF7E9A86175DB6A4" blockId="126.[128,2576,3295,3483]" pageId="126" pageNumber="885">
